    <h1>Audrey the Climber</h1>

    <h2>About Audrey</h2>
      <p>When we lived in California, we had few family sports we enjoyed. My wife and I would play tennis. The twins would play soccer. A few of us might play badminton out in the street between cars going by. But we rarely had family outdoor excursions, until I introduced my wife and kids to rock climbing.</p>

      <p>I had picked up rock climbing during my time as a missionary in France. We weren't normally allowed to do it because of the potential risks. But, we got special permission to do so with friends. We went to a long-abandoned granite mine West of the proven√ßale town, Aix en Provence. I had no equipment. 'Just started climbing barefoot. That began my love of the sport.</p>

